<item>
            <title>[HBASE-16432] Revisit the asynchronous ipc implementation</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-16432</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Seems the current approach of implementing AsyncTable is in trouble as we expose some netty classes in our public interfaces.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I agree that we should not do this. The AsyncTable should be implemented using the asynchronous protobuf stub, and we could use CompletableFuture or Deferred instead of netty&apos;s Future. I think the problem of netty&apos;s future is that it is tighten with netty&apos;s executor. This makes it impossible to use without netty.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12997824">HBASE-16432</key>
