                            <comment id="15425790" author="apache9" created="Thu, 18 Aug 2016 01:56:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;My plan is to do this with 3 steps&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1. Cut off the relationship between AsyncTable and Netty. We could implement the AsyncTable with protobuf async stub. After this the development of AsyncTable could continue since the async stub is already supported by the current AsyncRpcClient.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2. Add RpcChannel support for RpcClientImpl. The current implementation is wrong... We schedule a blocking task into the global event loop, this may block others as it is &apos;global&apos;...At this time, the AsyncTable can run on both RpcClientImpl and AsyncRpcClient.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;3. Do some refactoring on AbstractRpcClient and reimplement the AsyncRpcClient.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15425896" author="anoop.hbase" created="Thu, 18 Aug 2016 04:49:45 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Seems the current approach of implementing AsyncTable is in trouble as we expose some netty classes in our public interfaces.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Cut off the relationship between AsyncTable and Netty. We could implement the AsyncTable with protobuf async stub.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Means we will be exposing PB async stuff instead of netty?  That also should be avoided.  We should not be exposing any other third party class/interface directly&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15425904" author="apache9" created="Thu, 18 Aug 2016 05:01:27 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Means we will be exposing PB async stuff instead of netty?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Not necessary. The AsyncTable interface will use CompletableFuture or something like Deferred. The PB stuffs are only used in the implementation.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15425916" author="anoop.hbase" created="Thu, 18 Aug 2016 05:20:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;That is fine then&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15473759" author="apache9" created="Thu, 8 Sep 2016 12:38:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Resolve as all sub-tasks have been resolved. Let&apos;s move on.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
